  "text": "16 active uptake of barium into cells is not known [CITATION_1] . However, cellular Ca transporters rarely distinguish strongly against co-transport of Ba [CITATION_2] , and we postulate that barium uptake occurs in these surface waters in association with cells or organic matter that is not diatom-generated, and is then remineralised at shallow depths. This behaviour parallels NOx and PO 4 only in the upper 100m, below which the Ba d distribution resumes a more silica-like profile, indicating that the generally observed correlation between Ba d and skeletal material still occurs in this region, in layers below this unusual surface activity (Supplementary Information; Fig. S6 ).",
